Package uk.ac.susx.mlcl.lib.io

Classes for input and output operations such as using files, databases, or abstract data streams.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
CharChannel A channel that can read and write bytes.
DataSink Interface that is implemented by classes which consume arbitrary data and a semi structured mannar.
DataSource Interface that is implemented by classes which produce arbitrary data and a semi structured mannar.
FileFactory Define a factory method for the creation of files.
ObjectSink<T> Interface defining the acceptance of objects of the given type T.
ObjectSource<T> Defines a source of objects of some type T data.
ReadableCharChannel A channel that can read chars.
Seekable<P> Interface defining a data-store that can be random-accessed to some extent.
SeekableDataSource A DataSource that also supports random access through the position() methods.
SeekableObjectSource<T,P> Defines a source of objects of some type T data that is can be access in some form of random access.
WritableCharChannel A channel that can write chars.
 

Class Summary
CharFileChannel A class that gets round the problem of very large, seekable character files (greater than 2^31-1 bytes) by borrowing API from the FileChannel and from Java 7's NIO improvements.
Chunk<T> Chunk is a type of collections that implement ObjectSource.
Chunker<T,S extends ObjectSource<T>> Chunker is an ObjectSource adapter that buffers objects into fixed size chunks.
CountingObjectSink<S extends ObjectSink<T>,T> Wrapper sink that counts the number of objects consumed.
CountingObjectSource<S extends ObjectSource<T>,T> Wrapper source that counts the number of objects produced.
Files Static utility class for file manipulation.
ForwardingDataSink<T extends DataSink> A DataSink adapter that forwards all events to an encapsulated inner instance.
ForwardingDataSource<T extends DataSource> A DataSource adapter that forwards all method invocations to some encapsulated DataSource,
ForwardingObjectSink<S extends ObjectSink<T>,T> ObjectSink adapter that forwards all method invocations to some encapsulated instance.
ForwardingObjectSource<S extends ObjectSource<T>,T> An ObjectSource adapter that forwards all method invocations to an encapsulated inner instance.
ForwardingSeekableDataSource<S extends SeekableDataSource> A SeekableDataSource adapter that forwards all method invocations to some encapsulated inner class.
ForwardingSeekableObjectSource<S extends SeekableObjectSource<T,P>,T,P> A SeekableObjectSource adapter that forwards all method invocations to some encapsulated instance.
KFirstReducingObjectSink<T> Decorating ObjectSink that encapsulates some other instances, and filters the objects being consumed, such that only the first K sequential objects, that are equal according to some comparator, are actually forwarded to the encapsulated instance.
ObjectIO Static utility class for use with the ObjectSink and ObjectSource interfaces.
Tell Class used to store information about a position in randomly accessible source, such that the source can return to that position given only the data stored in Tell.
TempFileFactory A file FileFactory implementation that creates temporary files using File.createTempFile(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) to produce new files.
 

Package uk.ac.susx.mlcl.lib.io Description

Classes for input and output operations such as using files, databases, or abstract data streams.
